chmod <perm> <filename>  => to change file permissions
u , g , o 
+ , - 
r , w, x 
Example chmod u+rx,g+w,o-rwx file.txt
x  => 2^0 =1
w  => 2^1 =2
r  => 2^2 =4
chomd 740 file.txt
chown <user>:<group> <filename>  to change owner OR group OR both of a file
chown <user> <filename>
chown :<group> <filename>
chgrp <group> <filename>  to change the group of a file
chown/chmod -R <dirname> to change ownership or perm recursivly 
